sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J107058
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: BioBrick integrative vector targeting aspA locus
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: It has been derived from <partinfo>BBa_K300000</partinfo> base vector by exciding the default integration guide (attP of phi80 phage) and ligating aspA (<partinfo>BBa_C0083</partinfo>) as guide.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lorenzo Pasotti
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: It can be propagated in strains with pir or pir-116 locus. Integration works only in host strains with an intact aspA genomic locus.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: scar
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: XbaI/NheI mixed site without the initial CT nucleotides
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: It is the same as <partinfo>BBa_G0006</partinfo>, but it does not have the initial CT nucleotides. It is useful to submit XbaI/NheI fusions where the BioBrick with XbaI is a coding sequence (so XbaI is TCTAG instead of TCTAGAG).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lorenzo Pasotti
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Digested XbaI ligated with digested NheI.
